cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about neural abstractive summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new framework that involves global encoding, which is a technique used in deep learning models. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which could place it under cs.IR. Finally, the paper uses a convolutional gated unit, which is a type of neural network architecture, indicating that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
